  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Information Tracking and Monitoring for South Sudan Displacement Dynamics</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">With the overall objective of contributing to an enhanced understanding of mobility dynamics in South Sudan. IOM will continue to capture information on mobility trends and ensure the provision displacement-related data in order to ensure that humanitarian actors are positioned to plan timely and targeted interventions based on a solid evidence base. Under this project, IOM will maintain the largest displacement tracking and monitoring mechanism in the country: the Displacement Tracking Matrix (DTM). In order to do so, IOM will employ four interlinked and manually reinforcing tools and methodologies, namely: 1) flow monitoring, 2) intention surveys, 3) mobility tracking and 4) biometric registrations.</narrative>
  </description>
